Latvia’s Vilks Says Country to Meet Euro 2014 Goals, BNS Reports

-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 
2011-06-17T10:30:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/latvia-s-vilks-says-country-to-meet-euro-2014-goals-bns-reports.html
Latvia will meet all of the criteria
to adopt the euro in 2014, Finance Minister Andris Vilks said,
according to the  Baltic News Service .  “The question is will the euro zone at that moment be
ready to expand, and will some of the criteria have been
changed,” Vilks said, the Riga-based newswire reported.  The Baltic country plans to narrow its budget deficit to
2.5 percent of gross domestic product next year and adopt the
euro two years later.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor for this story:
Balazs Penz at   bpenz@bloomberg.net  